originalText.text: Worst gynecologist I have ever seen. I had to see her to get more birth control pills and she forced me to get a Pap. When the results of the Pap came back she didn’t warn me and did a biopsy. Turned out there was nothing wrong and she just cut out my flesh. I was in so much pain for three days and she didn’t even prescribe painkillers or apologize. Ended up taking two days off work. Seems like she doesn’t know what a woman should look like inside. I wouldn’t recommend her to anyone.

originalText.text: I saw Dr. Choe twice and was happy with her. She was gentle with my annual and very nice and friendly. I am giving 3 stars because of a recent experience where I was away on vacation and forgot my birth control. I reached out to the on-call emergency line and asked that my prescription be sent to the CVS closest to me. I was told that Dr. Choe was the on call doctor and did not see this as an emergency. Not only was I denied birth control while away on vacation, but Dr. Choe did not call me to explain the side effects of missing my birth control for x amount of days. She also never followed up with me. For this reason I will no longer be seeing her or anyone else in the Murray Hill Medical Group for fear that she will be the on call doctor when I have an emergency.

originalText.text: Unless you're willing to be assertive and to do the research necessary to advocate for your own gynecological health, I'd say steer clear of Dr. Choe and CareMount medical. The office staff are overworked and curt, and the doctor is insensitive and condescending. She demonstrated poor bedside manner and made me feel rushed and stupid for asking about possible alternatives to a procedure (which I ended up not needing). You're better off taking your time and money elsewhere.
